A close-up studio product visualization cross-section cutaway of a modular flight suit arm sleeve panel. The outermost layer is a 1.5mm active chameleon stealth skin composed of a flexible transparent hydrogel holding micro-etched horizontal channel rows of green and azure guanine nanocrystals. Directly beneath rests an amber-colored 1.0mm triboelectric fluoropolymer mesh with visible sliding micro-ridges. The structural core shows a dense 5.5mm aerospace-grade carbon fiber polycarbonate shell with integrated continuous graphene ground lines. The innermost face features a compliant, dark teal internal lining sleeve, realistic studio overhead cross-lighting, photorealistic material and resin textures, 8k --ar 16:9
